k.\n\n- Robert Louis Stevenson, Treasure Island\n|\nNever strike out of anger if at all possible, this will give your enemy the advantage and strengthen his resolve and psyche\n\n- Soke\n|\nLife is like a painting, seems smooth and glorious but you can see its dullness when you are near it.\n\n- Samiullah\n|\nHow far is too far? When you love a band so much that its songs fill the empty spaces inside your head and heart, is that too far?\n\n- Bert Murray, Colin Preston Rocked And Rolled\n|\nWe were like two atoms in one molecule, hydrogen and oxygen. Both explosive alone, but the source of everything when we came together.\n\n- Trevor D. Richardson, Dystopia Boy: The Unauthorized Files\n|\nFrom flophouse bedTo poorhouse bread,all outhouse sorrow:I thee wed.\n\n- Roman\n|\nWhat good is magic, if you can't use it to help people?\n\n- Tamora Pierce, Daja's Book\n|\nThe melodious song mesmerized me and cloaked my soul in a most liberating embrace I had never known. The emotion enveloped me, and smothered the emptiness.\n\n- J.D. Stroube, Caged in Spirit\n|\nThe pain we cause will haunt our memories and eat at our souls. I do not seek forgiveness, only the emptiness of death.\n\n- Harley\n|\nDesire. Enthusiasm. Purpose. Pleasure. Delight. Peace. Power. However you define passion, it is at the heart of your motivation.\n\n- Susan C. Young, The Art of Being: 8 Ways to Optimize Your Presence & Essence for Positive Impact\n|\n...if you're an actor, and you've thought your way into the part, then you're character portrayal will have authority...\n\n- John Geddes, A Familiar Rain\n|\nLess fear, more courage.Less doubt, more faith.Less talking, more action.Less ignorance, more knowledge.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nIf you make someone suffer today, without any doubt, you will be punished by your conscience. Don’t hurt anyone in anyway or form.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nI am of the opinion', Tharkay said, 'that you ought not assign to free will something more likely the consequence of a sharp blow to the skull.\n\n- Naomi Novik, Blood of Tyrants\n|\nIf you stay determined, the obstacles cannot stop your progress. You will triumph over every mountain.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Pearls of  Wisdom: Great  mind\n|\nIn the battle for possession of souls and worlds, it is likely that all serve to only one master.\n\n- Robert Neil Fleischer, Alien Biography\n|\nMaybe you should say goodbye, Cal.''No.''It might be important.''It might make her die.\n\n- Jenny Downham, Before I Die\n|\nPro-government press is not a press it is just a lie-generating ugly machine; it is a guard dog, guarding only the official thieves, not the public!\n\n- Mehmet\n|\nOne thing I’ve learnt about humans: you can’t judge their strength by the size of their actions, but by the devotion of an act, no matter how small.\n\n- Dianna Hardy, The Last Dragon\n|\nThere's a profit attached to every problem. Find it, face it and fix it.\n\n- Ifeanyi\n|\nReese sucked in a breath and played faster, hurling the anger through his fingers until it spun all hisfear, all his rage, into the gentle voice of music.\n\n- Willowy Whisper, This Hostile Land\n|\nCourage?' I gave a very soft laugh. 'I find courage is just another of life's illusions. In the end, we all do what we must.\n\n- Anthony  Ryan, Queen of Fire\n|\nWork hard, put maximum effort, and have a good attitude. Most importantly never give up.\n\n- Ana\n|\nThe only principle of Success in Life :'You must be present to win.\n\n- Abhysheq Shukla, KISS Life  'Life is what you make it'\n|\nThe existence of excessive nationalism is a symptom of a deeper problem in the collective consciousness, which is continually being exploited.\n\n- Bryant McGill, Voice of Reason\n|\nCourage is the most important of all the virtues because without courage, you can't practice any other virtue consistently.\n\n- Maya\n|\nBeneath the rust and grime which dulls the shine of our weathered hearts, joy patiently waits to be rediscovered\n\n- John\n|\nLife is an adventure, you only win if you are bold and courageous.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nA willing heart, daring spirit!\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nIf you can’t see a solution it does not mean it doesn’t exist, you are just blind to it\n\n- Harrish\n|\nTo lose a problem, do not oppose, let go of any need to control, perhaps it's all an illusion we project, more like a game we play than real?\n\n- Jay\n|\nGovernment should never be able to do anything you can't do. If you can't steal from your neighbor, you can't send the government to steal for you.\n\n- Ron\n|\nThe world doesn't owe you anything because you're in it, but you owe yourself the world because it is in you.\n\n- Kat Kaelin, TOOL OF THE WILLOW FAIRY: Love Will Find A Way\n|\n..A hawk soared over our carriage, letting out a high, piercing cry of defiance, and I wanted to jump out of the window and fly with it\n\n- Stephanie Burgis, Kat, Incorrigible\n|\nWhen someone hurts you, don't hurt him back but hit him with your unconditional love.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nYes, cannibals. People are just cannibals unless they leave each other alone.\n\n- Doris Lessing, The Golden Notebook\n|\nOne stone is enough to break a glass, One sentence is enough to break a heart,One smile is enough to fall in love,& one God is enough to live a fulfilling life..\n\n- KulsumAbdullah\n|\nChange the changeable, accept the unchangeable, and remove yourself from the unacceptable.\n\n- Denis\n|\nAs many ideas you can generate, encourage them to form nests in your mind, for one will surely liberate you.\n\n- Auliq-Ice\n|\nEveryday, you leave a footprint!\n\n- Ernest\n|\nI guess I need to leave it up to the Great Magician, as Harry would say.\n\n- Sofi Benitez, Dog Daze\n|\nWhen men decide in their secretly dark or hungry hearts to work their own will, there is little that can stop them. They have inner weather, sometimes unpredictable.\n\n- Linda Hogan, People of the Whale\n|\nThere are some wounds unreachable by words, some sins immune to apology.\n\n- Amy Hatvany, It Happens All the Time\n|\nSmoke rose straight up from the chimney, as if the house raised its hand. As if the house knew the answer.\n\n- Seré Prince Halverson, All the Winters After\n|\nForgiveness is a mystical act, not a reasonable one.\n\n- Caroline Myss, Defy Gravity: Healing Beyond the Bounds of Reason\n|\nI guess when you turn off the main road, you have to be prepared to see some funny houses.\n\n- Stephen\n|\nNever, Never give up, no matter what is you age, magick always is there. Use it!\n\n- Bobbie Kinkead, Rhyonna's Fright, A Faery's Challenge to Save Her Realm\n|\nI felt that thread that had come between us, tugging, tugging at my heart—so hard, it hurt me.\n\n- Sarah Waters, Fingersmith\n|\nYour emotional understanding about the preciousness of your human birth comes through conscious, repetitive mind training.\n\n- Tsoknyi Rinpoche, Solid Ground: Buddhist Wisdom for Difficult Times\n|\nThreatening a current or former partner isn't passion, or love, or heartache. It's violence, it's abuse and it's a crime.\n\n- Miya\n|\nDon't pretend to comfort me, my friend. I might also pretend to not let you down.\n\n- Toba Beta, Betelgeuse Incident: Insiden Bait Al-Jauza\n|\nSic vis pacem para bellum - if you want peace, prepare for war.\n\n- A.J. Darkholme, Rise of the Morningstar\n|\nA child falls many times in attempt to walk. But never quit trying and eventually, the child is able to walk.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nThis is where we should start focusing this conversation: how men (as readers, critics, and editors) can start to bear the responsibility for becoming better, broader readers.\n\n- Roxane Gay, Bad Feminist\n|\nThere's no better cure for the fear of taking after one's father, than not to know who he is.\n\n- André Gide, The Counterfeiters\n|\nIn this vast cosmic orchestra, peace is the music of every heart. Our glory lies in understanding, listening and honoring that music.\n\n- Amit Ray, Walking the